    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized analysis reveals a pronounced shift in US military posture toward unmanned systems integration and expanded ISR capabilities, as evidenced by the persistent presence of RC-135 Rivet Joint aircraft conducting SIGINT/COMINT operations. These platforms are likely serving as control nodes for emerging drone integration efforts, particularly in European and Pacific theaters, aligning with broader modernization trends. The Gulf Coast and European airspace show heightened activity, with multiple TEX2, BE20, and A400 platforms indicating routine naval aviation training, maritime patrol, and NATO logistics support. The establishment of the Army&#39;s Multi-Domain Command-Pacific and USARPAC&#39;s new drone-focused unit underscores a strategic pivot toward overwhelming adversary capabilities in A2/AD environments, particularly in the Pacific. Concurrently, the arrival of the VC-25B Bridge jet at the Presidential Airlift Group signals continued investment in high-priority strategic transport. While naval vessel positions remain unverified in the provided data, the aircraft patterns suggest active carrier strike group operations in the Mediterranean and Pacific, with a focus on maintaining readiness and expanding unmanned system integration. The absence of explicit fleet data limits full assessment, but the observed trends indicate a deliberate emphasis on ISR expansion, drone integration, and theater-specific readiness, particularly in response to evolving regional threats.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
